text.tspan: Welcome to the Student Robotics Competition 2022!

flowRoot.flowPara: Student Robotics is a volunteer based organisation that challenges teams of 16 to 19 year-olds to design, build, and program fully autonomous robots to compete in our free-to-enter annual competition.
For more information and live scores, visit: srobo.org

When in a team’s scoring zone, correctly oriented cans are worth 3 points, upside down cans are worth one point, and cans lying on their side are worth nothing. Tin cans on the arena floor start upside down, but those on the raised platform in the centre are already the right way up. Robots can detect a can’s orientation by the coloured insulating band along the bottom.
